1
00:00:02,645 --> 00:00:05,812
-ONCE UPON A TIME,
THERE WAS A MAN WHO DIED.

2
00:00:05,812 --> 00:00:09,312
THE STORY THE MAN WROTE
WAS ABOUT A HAPPY PRINCE

3
00:00:09,312 --> 00:00:13,345
WHO LOVED EVERYONE
AND WAS LOVED BY EVERYONE.

4
00:00:13,345 --> 00:00:17,578
THE PEOPLE FOUGHT, EACH WANTING
HIM TO LOVE THEM AND THEM ALONE,

5
00:00:17,578 --> 00:00:20,712
AND AN EVIL RAVEN PECKED
AT THE LOVING HEARTS

6
00:00:20,712 --> 00:00:23,712
OF ONE PERSON AFTER ANOTHER.

7
00:00:23,712 --> 00:00:27,245
THE MORE THE PRINCE LOVED THEM
AND TRIED TO SAVE THEM,

8
00:00:27,245 --> 00:00:30,345
THE MORE THE PEOPLE'S LOVE
JUST FED THE RAVEN.

9
00:00:30,345 --> 00:00:33,278
IN THE END, THE RAVEN THOUGHT,

10
00:00:33,278 --> 00:00:36,445
"I'D LIKE TO TRY
EATING THE PRINCE'S HEART,

11
00:00:36,445 --> 00:00:39,945
THE MOST DELICIOUS ONE OF ALL."

12
00:00:39,945 --> 00:00:42,978
[ RITSUKO OKAZAKI'S
"MORNING GRACE" PLAYS ]

13
00:00:54,112 --> 00:00:57,145
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

14
00:02:29,816 --> 00:02:32,316
-[ OWL HOOTING ]
-THANK YOU.

15
00:02:32,316 --> 00:02:34,649
-HEY.

16
00:02:34,649 --> 00:02:38,016
[ TWINKLE ]

17
00:02:38,016 --> 00:02:40,682
-ALL RIGHT.
JUST WHAT'S GOING ON?

18
00:02:40,682 --> 00:02:42,149
AND WHO IS SHE?

19
00:02:42,149 --> 00:02:44,016
WHY DID THE STORY JUST --

20
00:02:44,016 --> 00:02:47,516
-I WILL MAKE SURE
IT DOESN'T DOUBLE BACK AGAIN.

21
00:02:47,516 --> 00:02:50,816
-FAKIR, WHAT ARE YOU
TRYING TO ACCOMPLISH?

22
00:02:50,816 --> 00:02:51,982
WAIT A MINUTE!

23
00:02:51,982 --> 00:02:53,549
YOU'RE NOT THINKING
OF REWRITING THE STORY

24
00:02:53,549 --> 00:02:55,016
THAT'S CONTROLLING THIS TOWN,
ARE YOU?

25
00:02:55,016 --> 00:02:57,749
-ALL I WANT IS THE POWER
TO PROTECT PEOPLE.

26
00:02:57,749 --> 00:02:58,749
THAT'S IT.

27
00:02:58,749 --> 00:03:01,916
AUTOR, CAN I ASK YOU SOMETHING?

28
00:03:01,916 --> 00:03:02,982
-WHAT'S THAT?

29
00:03:02,982 --> 00:03:05,449
-MY POWER --
IS IT REALLY SOMETHING

30
00:03:05,449 --> 00:03:07,516
THAT MAKES STORIES INTO REALITY?

31
00:03:07,516 --> 00:03:09,382
YOU'RE SURE
I'M NOT WRITING THINGS

32
00:03:09,382 --> 00:03:10,982
THAT WILL BECOME REALITY ANYWAY?

33
00:03:10,982 --> 00:03:13,149
-THE TWO ARE PART
OF THE SAME POWER.

34
00:03:13,149 --> 00:03:14,149
LISTEN TO ME.

35
00:03:14,149 --> 00:03:15,449
IF YOUR POWER IS IMMATURE,

36
00:03:15,449 --> 00:03:17,482
THEN OF COURSE IT'S GOING TO BE
SWAYED BY REALITY.

37
00:03:17,482 --> 00:03:19,516
BUT IF YOU DEVELOP
A STRONG POWER,

38
00:03:19,516 --> 00:03:20,716
REALITY SHOULD START

39
00:03:20,716 --> 00:03:23,216
BENDING TOWARDS
AND OBEYING YOUR STORIES.

40
00:03:23,216 --> 00:03:26,149
IT WOULD THEN BE
A TRIVIAL MATTER TO MOVE ON

41
00:03:26,149 --> 00:03:28,949
TO MANIPULATING THE FATES
OF ALL MANKIND.

42
00:03:36,716 --> 00:03:40,216
-[ SIGHS ]

43
00:03:40,216 --> 00:03:44,049
-[ Thinking ]
THE POWER TO PROTECT, EH?

44
00:03:44,049 --> 00:03:46,182
DID I ACTUALLY
WRITE DOWN A STORY

45
00:03:46,182 --> 00:03:48,349
THAT SAVED HER
WITH MY OWN POWER,

46
00:03:48,349 --> 00:03:51,449
OR WAS I MADE TO WRITE IT?

47
00:03:53,282 --> 00:03:56,116
HER FEELINGS FOR MYTHO
ARE SPILLING UP

48
00:03:56,116 --> 00:03:58,382
THROUGH MY HANDS
AND OUT ONTO THE PAGE.

49
00:03:58,382 --> 00:04:01,016
EVEN THOUGH
I COULDN'T WRITE ONE LETTER

50
00:04:01,016 --> 00:04:02,549
OF A STORY ABOUT MYTHO,

51
00:04:02,549 --> 00:04:04,749
I COULD WRITE A STORY
TO SAVE HER,

52
00:04:04,749 --> 00:04:06,549
AS IF IT WERE FLOWING FROM ME.

53
00:04:06,549 --> 00:04:10,682
BUT THE STORY I NEED TO WRITE
IS ABOUT MYTHO.

54
00:04:10,682 --> 00:04:12,116
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

55
00:04:14,782 --> 00:04:17,282
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

56
00:04:17,282 --> 00:04:19,449
-[ GROANS LIGHTLY ]

57
00:04:19,449 --> 00:04:21,016
I'M AT FAKIR'S?

58
00:04:25,949 --> 00:04:30,749
THAT MANUSCRIPT --
HE SAID HE WROTE THAT FOR ME.

59
00:04:30,749 --> 00:04:32,682
[ DOOR OPENS ]

60
00:04:32,682 --> 00:04:34,382
OH, UZURA!

61
00:04:34,382 --> 00:04:37,782
I GUESS YOU GOT BACK SAFE,
TOO, HUH?

62
00:04:37,782 --> 00:04:41,482
-[ EXHALES ]

63
00:04:41,482 --> 00:04:42,649
-FAKIR!

64
00:04:42,649 --> 00:04:44,982
-SO, YOU'RE AWAKE.
YOU'RE HUNGRY, RIGHT?

65
00:04:44,982 --> 00:04:46,316
-YEAH.

66
00:04:46,316 --> 00:04:47,482
[ GASPS ]

67
00:04:47,482 --> 00:04:50,249
BUT THAT'S THE STORY YOU WROTE.

68
00:04:50,249 --> 00:04:52,982
-IT'S A STORY THAT'S OVER NOW.

69
00:04:52,982 --> 00:04:56,849
-[ Thinking ] THE STORY ABOUT ME
THAT FAKIR WROTE FOR ME.

70
00:04:56,849 --> 00:05:00,016
I KIND OF WANTED TO READ IT,

71
00:05:00,016 --> 00:05:04,149
BUT I'M REALLY GLAD YOU'RE ABLE
TO WRITE STORIES NOW, FAKIR.

72
00:05:04,149 --> 00:05:05,482
[ SWALLOWS FOOD ]

73
00:05:05,482 --> 00:05:07,916
AND THEN WHEN I TOLD HIM
THAT I THOUGHT THE FIVE GATES

74
00:05:07,916 --> 00:05:10,316
HAD HEART SHARDS IN THEM,
HE SAID, "CONGRATULATIONS."

75
00:05:10,316 --> 00:05:11,882
-SO, BASICALLY, THOSE SHARDS

76
00:05:11,882 --> 00:05:14,216
ARE THE ONLY ONES
SEALING AWAY THE RAVEN.

77
00:05:14,216 --> 00:05:16,116
-NOW WE CAN GO AND GET THEM ALL.

78
00:05:16,116 --> 00:05:17,782
MM!
-WE COULD.

79
00:05:17,782 --> 00:05:19,649
IT WOULD ALSO RESTORE THE RAVEN.

80
00:05:19,649 --> 00:05:21,649
-HM? HM! [ CHOKES ]

81
00:05:21,649 --> 00:05:23,649
[ COUGHS ]
-CALM DOWN, WILL YOU?

82
00:05:23,649 --> 00:05:25,149
-HM! NHM!

83
00:05:25,149 --> 00:05:26,916
-IT'S A BRIDGE
WE'LL HAVE TO CROSS EVENTUALLY.

84
00:05:26,916 --> 00:05:28,116
AND IF WE DON'T GET MOVING,

85
00:05:28,116 --> 00:05:29,682
MYTHO MIGHT NOT BE ABLE
TO RETURN TO NORMAL.

86
00:05:29,682 --> 00:05:31,016
-YEAH, THAT'S TRUE!

87
00:05:31,016 --> 00:05:33,149
I GUESS EVEN IF
THE RAVEN IS RESTORED,

88
00:05:33,149 --> 00:05:34,616
IT'LL BE NO PROBLEM NOW

89
00:05:34,616 --> 00:05:37,416
THAT YOU'VE GOT
THE POWER OF STORIES, RIGHT?

90
00:05:37,416 --> 00:05:41,016
-YOU DO YOUR BEST.

91
00:05:41,016 --> 00:05:42,349
-[ Thinking ] THAT'S RIGHT.

92
00:05:42,349 --> 00:05:45,182
MYTHO HAS FAKIR,
AND HE HAS PRINCESS TUTU.

93
00:05:45,182 --> 00:05:47,516
HE'LL NEVER LOSE TO THE RAVEN!

94
00:05:47,516 --> 00:05:50,016
AND I'M SURE
RUE WILL RETURN TO NORMAL, TOO.

95
00:05:50,016 --> 00:05:52,349
[ GASPS ]

96
00:05:52,349 --> 00:05:53,816
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

97
00:05:53,816 --> 00:05:55,549
[ GASPS ] RUE?

98
00:05:55,549 --> 00:05:59,216
[ CROWS CAWING ]

99
00:05:59,216 --> 00:06:02,382
-GOOD MORNING, PRINCE.

100
00:06:02,382 --> 00:06:03,816
-PRINCE, HUH?

101
00:06:03,816 --> 00:06:04,849
HUH.

102
00:06:09,716 --> 00:06:11,216
HM?

103
00:06:11,216 --> 00:06:14,016
-PRINCE, YOU'RE HUNGRY,
AREN'T YOU?

104
00:06:14,016 --> 00:06:16,882
[ GASPS ]

105
00:06:21,649 --> 00:06:23,449
[ GASPS ]
[ MOUSE SQUEALING ]

106
00:06:23,449 --> 00:06:24,682
[ GASPS ]
-[ GASPS ]

107
00:06:24,682 --> 00:06:26,682
[ SQUEALING CONTINUES ]

108
00:06:26,682 --> 00:06:29,349
-HELLO, KRAEHE.

109
00:06:29,349 --> 00:06:31,949
YES, I AM HUNGRY.

110
00:06:31,949 --> 00:06:33,282
-[ GASPS ] STOP!

111
00:06:33,282 --> 00:06:34,682
[ SQUEALING CONTINUES ]

112
00:06:34,682 --> 00:06:36,849
[ PANTING ]

113
00:06:36,849 --> 00:06:38,582
-NOW, WHAT DID YOU DO THAT FOR?

114
00:06:38,582 --> 00:06:39,982
YOU LOVE ME, DON'T YOU?

115
00:06:42,016 --> 00:06:44,182
YOU DON'T LOVE ME?

116
00:06:44,182 --> 00:06:48,516
-MY LOVE HAS DONE NOTHING
BUT MAKE YOU INTO THIS.

117
00:06:48,516 --> 00:06:51,116
[ Thinking ]
I HAVE NO RIGHT TO LOVE YOU.

118
00:06:51,116 --> 00:06:52,516
[ WHIMPERS ]

119
00:06:52,516 --> 00:06:54,849
-IS THAT...MYTHO?

120
00:06:54,849 --> 00:06:59,182
-LET'S DANCE...MY PRINCE.

121
00:06:59,182 --> 00:07:02,682
-OF COURSE.

122
00:07:02,682 --> 00:07:04,449
-OH, PRINCE.

123
00:07:04,449 --> 00:07:08,449
-I DON'T THINK I'VE EVER SEEN
RUE DANCE SO -- SO SADLY.

124
00:07:08,449 --> 00:07:11,749
-DO YOU REMEMBER ALL THE
PAS DE DEUX WE DANCED TOGETHER?

125
00:07:14,016 --> 00:07:17,349
YOU'RE MY PRINCE.

126
00:07:17,349 --> 00:07:18,849
-THAT'S RIGHT.

127
00:07:18,849 --> 00:07:21,882
-YEP. AFTER ALL,
THAT'S WHAT FATHER SAID.

128
00:07:21,882 --> 00:07:26,049
-THE PRINCE WHO SEALED ME AWAY
DESERVES OUR HATRED.

129
00:07:26,049 --> 00:07:27,916
[ GROWLS ]

130
00:07:27,916 --> 00:07:32,916
BUT...HE IS THE ONE PRINCE
THAT YOU SHOULD MARRY, KRAEHE.

131
00:07:32,916 --> 00:07:34,082
-HUH?

132
00:07:34,082 --> 00:07:37,016
-A PRINCE WHO LOVES EVERYONE
SHOULD BE ABLE

133
00:07:37,016 --> 00:07:40,582
TO SINCERELY LOVE EVEN
AN UGLY, PITIFUL GIRL LIKE YOU.

134
00:07:40,582 --> 00:07:42,249
-YOU REALLY THINK?

135
00:07:42,249 --> 00:07:45,082
-YES. I REALLY DO.

136
00:07:45,082 --> 00:07:47,249
-[ Thinking ]
THE ONLY TIME I WAS HAPPY

137
00:07:47,249 --> 00:07:49,582
WAS THE TIME
THAT I SPENT WITH YOU.

138
00:07:52,682 --> 00:07:55,116
-MYTHO? MYTHO?

139
00:07:55,116 --> 00:07:57,782
-[ Thinking ] I WANTED YOU
TO LOOK AT ME ALONE.

140
00:07:57,782 --> 00:08:00,116
I WANTED
NEVER TO BE WITHOUT YOU,

141
00:08:00,116 --> 00:08:01,449
NOT EVEN FOR A MOMENT.

142
00:08:01,449 --> 00:08:03,116
SAY, LOOK, IS THIS PRETTY?

143
00:08:03,116 --> 00:08:04,616
-YES.

144
00:08:04,616 --> 00:08:06,682
I HAVE TO GET BACK
TO FAKIR'S SOON.

145
00:08:06,682 --> 00:08:08,082
HE'LL BE GETTING WORRIED.

146
00:08:08,082 --> 00:08:09,716
-WHAT? WAIT. WATCH ME!

147
00:08:09,716 --> 00:08:11,749
-I'M SORRY.

148
00:08:11,749 --> 00:08:13,982
-[ Voice breaking ]
NO! STAY AND WATCH ME, PLEASE!

149
00:08:13,982 --> 00:08:16,716
I PRACTICED AS HARD AS I COULD!

150
00:08:16,716 --> 00:08:19,249
[ Thinking ]
BUT YOU -- YOU DIDN'T.

151
00:08:19,249 --> 00:08:23,749
-KRAEHE, GO TO THE HUMAN WORLD
AS A HUMAN GIRL

152
00:08:23,749 --> 00:08:25,749
AND WIN THE PRINCE'S LOVE.

153
00:08:25,749 --> 00:08:27,082
-YES, FATHER.

154
00:08:27,082 --> 00:08:28,782
-AND IF YOU SHOULD EVER GET HOLD

155
00:08:28,782 --> 00:08:30,882
OF A SHARD
OF THE PRINCE'S HEART,

156
00:08:30,882 --> 00:08:33,149
I NEED YOU
TO BRING IT TO ME AT ONCE

157
00:08:33,149 --> 00:08:36,349
BECAUSE I HAVE A TASK TO PERFORM
IN PREPARATION

158
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:38,749
FOR YOUR WEDDING TO HIM.
-I WILL.

159
00:08:38,749 --> 00:08:41,182
-TODAY IS THE FIRST DAY
OF LESSONS

160
00:08:41,182 --> 00:08:43,616
FOR THOSE
IN THE BEGINNERS' CLASS,

161
00:08:43,616 --> 00:08:48,782
SO I'LL TAKE THIS TIME TO TALK
ABOUT BALLET AND MARRIAGE.

162
00:08:48,782 --> 00:08:51,716
BALLET AND MARRIAGE
ARE INEXTRICABLY...

163
00:08:51,716 --> 00:08:52,916
-HELLO, RUE.

164
00:08:52,916 --> 00:08:55,916
-WE CAN SEE EACH OTHER
EVERY DAY NOW, MY PRINCE.

165
00:08:55,916 --> 00:08:57,316
-MYTHO.
-HM?

166
00:08:57,316 --> 00:08:58,782
-CALL MYTHO "PRINCE" AGAIN,

167
00:08:58,782 --> 00:09:00,716
AND I'LL MAKE SURE
YOU REGRET IT.

168
00:09:00,716 --> 00:09:04,349
-THEN I WON'T DO IT AS LONG AS
YOU AGREE NOT TO GET IN OUR WAY.

169
00:09:04,349 --> 00:09:05,549
-[ SCOFFS ]

170
00:09:05,549 --> 00:09:08,216
-I DIDN'T WANT ANYONE
TO KNOW I WAS A CROW,

171
00:09:08,216 --> 00:09:11,216
SO I SEALED AWAY THEIR MEMORIES.

172
00:09:11,216 --> 00:09:13,682
-MY BELOVED DAUGHTER...

173
00:09:13,682 --> 00:09:15,316
-[ Voice breaking ]
I HONESTLY WAS CONVINCED

174
00:09:15,316 --> 00:09:17,816
THAT I WAS FATHER'S DAUGHTER.

175
00:09:17,816 --> 00:09:20,349
[ SOBBING ]

176
00:09:20,349 --> 00:09:22,016
I'M A FOOL.

177
00:09:22,016 --> 00:09:24,149
THERE'S NO WAY
A MERE HUMAN LIKE ME

178
00:09:24,149 --> 00:09:26,449
COULD MARRY THE PRINCE
FROM THE STORY.

179
00:09:26,449 --> 00:09:30,616
-SO ALL THIS TIME,
RUE REALLY WASN'T KRAEHE AT ALL.

180
00:09:30,616 --> 00:09:34,349
-SHALL WE DANCE, KRAEHE?

181
00:09:34,349 --> 00:09:37,949
-[ SOBBING ]
-[ GASPS ]

182
00:09:41,982 --> 00:09:44,016
-[ CONTINUES SOBBING ]

183
00:09:51,782 --> 00:09:53,282
-RUE?

184
00:09:53,282 --> 00:09:54,516
-DUCK?

185
00:09:54,516 --> 00:09:57,349
-WHY DOES MYTHO LOOK LIKE THAT?

186
00:09:57,349 --> 00:09:59,182
-YOU SAW?
-UH, UNH...

187
00:09:59,182 --> 00:10:01,182
-THAT'S RIGHT.
IT WAS MY FAULT.

188
00:10:01,182 --> 00:10:02,516
-HUH?
-GO AHEAD.

189
00:10:02,516 --> 00:10:04,682
LAUGH AT THE FOOLISH GIRL
TRICKED BY A RAVEN.

190
00:10:04,682 --> 00:10:06,416
-I WOULDN'T LAUGH AT YOU.
-LIAR!

191
00:10:06,416 --> 00:10:08,749
I KNOW YOU'RE THINKING
THIS SERVES ME RIGHT.

192
00:10:08,749 --> 00:10:10,749
-NO, I'M NOT.

193
00:10:10,749 --> 00:10:12,416
-LEAVE ME BE.

194
00:10:12,416 --> 00:10:15,082
-RUE, INSIDE THE FIVE TOWN GATES

195
00:10:15,082 --> 00:10:17,982
ARE THE HEART SHARDS
THAT ARE SEALING AWAY THE RAVEN.

196
00:10:17,982 --> 00:10:21,649
IF WE RETURN THEM, I KNOW
MYTHO WILL GO BACK TO NORMAL.

197
00:10:21,649 --> 00:10:24,149
-BUT THEY'RE
SEALING THE RAVEN AWAY?

198
00:10:24,149 --> 00:10:26,082
N-NO! YOU MUSTN'T!
-WHAT?

199
00:10:26,082 --> 00:10:27,949
-SHOULD THE RAVEN BE RESTORED

200
00:10:27,949 --> 00:10:30,949
AND THE PRINCE GET HIS HEART
IN ITS ENTIRETY,

201
00:10:30,949 --> 00:10:34,182
HE'LL GIVE HIS HEART
OVER TO THE RAVEN.

202
00:10:34,182 --> 00:10:35,549
-WHAT?

203
00:10:35,549 --> 00:10:38,982
BUT IF THE PRINCE
GOES BACK TO NORMAL --

204
00:10:38,982 --> 00:10:41,316
-WHAT IF HE DOESN'T GO BACK
TO NORMAL?! WHAT THEN?!

205
00:10:41,316 --> 00:10:43,149
-BUT I-I --
-THE RAVEN WAS USING US

206
00:10:43,149 --> 00:10:45,216
TO MAKE THE PRINCE
GIVE HIM HIS HEART!

207
00:10:45,216 --> 00:10:46,382
THAT'S ALL HE WANTED!

208
00:10:46,382 --> 00:10:47,882
-NO, WAIT, BUT THEN --

209
00:10:47,882 --> 00:10:50,549
-LISTEN TO ME!
DON'T DO ANYTHING ELSE!

210
00:10:50,549 --> 00:10:51,682
-RUE, I --

211
00:10:51,682 --> 00:10:56,516
-[ Crying ] I'M BEGGING YOU.
PLEASE STOP.

212
00:10:56,516 --> 00:10:59,682
IF IT WERE ME,
IF I WERE PRINCESS TUTU,

213
00:10:59,682 --> 00:11:02,549
I'D NEVER GIVE HIM
HIS HEART BACK.

214
00:11:02,549 --> 00:11:05,416
-[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

215
00:11:05,416 --> 00:11:07,749
NOW WHAT?

216
00:11:07,749 --> 00:11:09,749
WHAT SHOULD I DO?

217
00:11:09,749 --> 00:11:12,016
-WHAT A SHAME FOR YOU,
LITTLE DUCK.

218
00:11:12,016 --> 00:11:14,649
THE STORY WON'T END
THAT EASILY, YOU KNOW?

219
00:11:14,649 --> 00:11:17,249
FIRST, THAT'S NOT NEARLY
TRAGIC ENOUGH.

220
00:11:17,249 --> 00:11:18,449
[ CHUCKLES ]

221
00:11:32,884 --> 00:11:35,195
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

222
00:11:35,195 --> 00:11:36,528
-NOW WHAT?

223
00:11:36,528 --> 00:11:38,328
QUACK!
[ TWINKLE ]

224
00:11:38,328 --> 00:11:39,495
[ Weakly ] QUACK.

225
00:11:39,495 --> 00:11:42,462
-WHAT'S WRONG WITH DUCK, ZURA?

226
00:11:42,462 --> 00:11:43,728
-DUCK DOESN'T KNOW.

227
00:11:43,728 --> 00:11:46,895
-HUH? THAT'S MYSELF
AS A PUPPET, ZURA.

228
00:11:46,895 --> 00:11:48,495
-THERE'S A THING
SHE DOESN'T KNOW.

229
00:11:48,495 --> 00:11:50,762
-A THING, ZURA?

230
00:11:50,762 --> 00:11:53,162
-A TRUTH THAT SHOULD'VE BEEN
REVEALED

231
00:11:53,162 --> 00:11:56,495
AFTER THE PRINCE'S HEART
WAS STOLEN BY THE RAVEN.

232
00:11:56,495 --> 00:11:59,728
-THE PRINCE FROM "THE PRINCE
AND THE RAVEN" HAS BECOME REAL.

233
00:11:59,728 --> 00:12:01,728
[ CUP AND SAUCER CLATTERING ]
I SEE.

234
00:12:01,728 --> 00:12:03,895
AND THE RAVEN HAS BECOME REAL,
AS WELL,

235
00:12:03,895 --> 00:12:05,828
AND IS BEING RESTORED
AS WE SPEAK!

236
00:12:05,828 --> 00:12:08,762
THIS TOWN REALLY
IS BEING CONTROLLED BY STORIES.

237
00:12:08,762 --> 00:12:11,228
MY HYPOTHESIS
WAS RIGHT ON THE MARK!

238
00:12:11,228 --> 00:12:14,495
-I'M A KNIGHT WHO WAS GIVEN
THE FATE OF DEATH IN VAIN.

239
00:12:14,495 --> 00:12:17,462
MY SWORD WOULD PROVE USELESS
IN PROTECTING THE PRINCE.

240
00:12:17,462 --> 00:12:19,795
-SO YOU WANT TO WRITE?
-YES.

241
00:12:19,795 --> 00:12:22,628
-WELL, TO BE FRANK,
YOU HAVE NO HOPE OF REWRITING

242
00:12:22,628 --> 00:12:24,928
DROSSELMEYER'S STORIES
AT YOUR LEVEL OF POWER.

243
00:12:24,928 --> 00:12:26,428
-[ SCOFFS ]

244
00:12:26,428 --> 00:12:28,995
-IF YOU'RE ONLY WHERE THE STORY
IS WRITING ITSELF THROUGH YOU,

245
00:12:28,995 --> 00:12:31,362
THEN THERE'S NO WAY YOU COULD
MAKE YOUR STORIES REALITY.

246
00:12:31,362 --> 00:12:33,362
-I'M AWARE OF THAT!

247
00:12:33,362 --> 00:12:36,362
THAT'S WHY I'M ASKING YOU
FOR YOUR HELP, AUTOR.

248
00:12:36,362 --> 00:12:38,628
-AND JUST WHY SHOULD
I HAVE TO DO THAT FOR YOU?

249
00:12:38,628 --> 00:12:40,762
-LISTEN, I NEED YOUR KNOWLEDGE.

250
00:12:40,762 --> 00:12:42,628
-AND ALL I'M SAYING IS,
WHY SHOULD I?

251
00:12:42,628 --> 00:12:44,962
-QUACK.

252
00:12:44,962 --> 00:12:46,628
[ SIGHS ]

253
00:12:46,628 --> 00:12:49,128
MYTHO -- WHAT DOES MYTHO
WANT ME TO DO?

254
00:12:49,128 --> 00:12:51,295
[ SNARE DRUM TAPS ]
UNH? QUACK.

255
00:12:51,295 --> 00:12:52,628
UZURA!

256
00:12:52,628 --> 00:12:55,462
-YOU'RE GOING TO STOP
BEING DUCK, AREN'T YOU, ZURA?

257
00:12:55,462 --> 00:12:57,795
-QUACK?

258
00:12:57,795 --> 00:13:00,028
-MYSELF TOLD ME SO, ZURA.

259
00:13:00,028 --> 00:13:01,662
-MYSELF?

260
00:13:03,695 --> 00:13:07,695
QUA-QUA -- QUACK-QUACK-QUACK!

261
00:13:07,695 --> 00:13:11,095
QUACK!
-MYSELF IS HERE INSIDE ME, ZURA.

262
00:13:11,095 --> 00:13:13,595
-[ GRUNTS LIGHTLY ]

263
00:13:13,595 --> 00:13:16,595
[ Thinking ]
THE SOUND OF UZURA'S HEART.

264
00:13:16,595 --> 00:13:18,162
[ GEARS GRINDING,
WALTZ PLAYING ]

265
00:13:18,162 --> 00:13:23,328
THIS MUSIC IS...
[GASPS] MISS EDEL!

266
00:13:23,328 --> 00:13:26,062
-IT'S BEEN A WHILE,
HASN'T IT, DUCK?

267
00:13:26,062 --> 00:13:28,395
-MISS EDEL!

268
00:13:28,395 --> 00:13:31,728
-THERE'S A THING
THAT DUCK DOESN'T KNOW.

269
00:13:31,728 --> 00:13:32,928
-WHAT?

270
00:13:32,928 --> 00:13:35,228
-THE DUCK'S PENDANT.

271
00:13:35,228 --> 00:13:37,228
-MY PENDANT?

272
00:13:37,228 --> 00:13:40,895
-YES. THAT'S THE LAST
OF THE PRINCE'S HEART SHARDS.

273
00:13:40,895 --> 00:13:41,962
-[ GASPS ]

274
00:13:41,962 --> 00:13:44,362
-IT RESONATES
WITH THE HEART SHARDS

275
00:13:44,362 --> 00:13:46,795
BECAUSE IT IS
A HEART SHARD ITSELF.

276
00:13:46,795 --> 00:13:50,962
THAT SHARD IS WHAT AWAKENS
PRINCESS TUTU.

277
00:13:50,962 --> 00:13:53,628
PRINCESS TUTU -- THE ONLY ONE

278
00:13:53,628 --> 00:13:56,562
WHO CAN GIVE THE PRINCE'S HEART
BACK TO HIM.

279
00:13:56,562 --> 00:13:57,595
-I GET IT.

280
00:13:57,595 --> 00:13:59,628
BEFORE THE PRINCE
SHATTERED HIS HEART,

281
00:13:59,628 --> 00:14:01,995
IT WAS HIS WILL
THAT HE'D SOMEDAY GET IT BACK.

282
00:14:01,995 --> 00:14:03,495
ISN'T THAT RIGHT?

283
00:14:03,495 --> 00:14:06,095
-HOWEVER, WHETHER OR NOT
THE DUCK RETURNS

284
00:14:06,095 --> 00:14:09,762
THAT HEART SHARD TO THE PRINCE
DEPENDS ON HER OWN WILL.

285
00:14:09,762 --> 00:14:12,595
-MISS EDEL.

286
00:14:12,595 --> 00:14:15,595
[ Thinking ]
MY WILL IS THE SAME AS MYTHO'S.

287
00:14:15,595 --> 00:14:17,595
QUACK.

288
00:14:17,595 --> 00:14:19,828
-YOU LOOK LIKE
YOU FEEL BETTER, ZURA.

289
00:14:22,362 --> 00:14:23,495
[ EXHALES ]

290
00:14:23,495 --> 00:14:26,495
-QUACK!

291
00:14:26,495 --> 00:14:28,195
[ TWINKLE ]

292
00:14:33,128 --> 00:14:36,895
-THE PENDANT -- YOU'RE GIVING IT
TO THE PRINCE, ZURA?

293
00:14:36,895 --> 00:14:38,062
-MM-HMM.

294
00:14:38,062 --> 00:14:40,362
-AND THEN YOU'LL GO BACK
TO BEING A DUCK, ZURA?

295
00:14:40,362 --> 00:14:41,728
-MM-HMM.

296
00:14:41,728 --> 00:14:43,895
-[ Voice breaking ]
AND THEN WE WON'T BE ABLE

297
00:14:43,895 --> 00:14:45,728
TO TALK TO EACH OTHER
ANYMORE, ZURA?

298
00:14:45,728 --> 00:14:48,062
-MM-HMM.

299
00:14:48,062 --> 00:14:50,795
[ TEARS TAPPING SNARE ]
-AND EVEN IF...

300
00:14:50,795 --> 00:14:52,262
-[ GASPS ]

301
00:14:52,262 --> 00:14:56,928
-...EVEN IF I PUT WATER ON YOU,
YOU WON'T CHANGE BACK, ZURA?

302
00:14:56,928 --> 00:14:59,495
-YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT.

303
00:14:59,495 --> 00:15:01,428
THAT ME IS THE REAL ME.

304
00:15:01,428 --> 00:15:03,562
-YOU'RE REALLY A DUCK, ZURA?

305
00:15:03,562 --> 00:15:04,828
-MM-HMM.

306
00:15:04,828 --> 00:15:06,962
NOW, DON'T CRY, OKAY?

307
00:15:06,962 --> 00:15:09,795
-OKAY, ZURA.

308
00:15:09,795 --> 00:15:11,295
-UZURA! NO!

309
00:15:11,295 --> 00:15:13,562
THAT CURSED EDEL HAD TO BUTT IN.

310
00:15:13,562 --> 00:15:16,728
THAT WAS THE SECRET I WAS SAVING
FOR MY LAST BIT OF FUN.

311
00:15:16,728 --> 00:15:19,162
WELL, NO MATTER,
WITH THINGS AS THEY ARE,

312
00:15:19,162 --> 00:15:22,095
THEY WON'T BE ABLE
TO ESCAPE THE TRAGEDY.

313
00:15:22,095 --> 00:15:23,762
-AAAH!

314
00:15:23,762 --> 00:15:27,395
AAH-AH!

315
00:15:27,395 --> 00:15:30,128
AH-AH!

316
00:15:30,128 --> 00:15:32,528
[ GRUNTING ]

317
00:15:32,528 --> 00:15:34,162
AAAH!

318
00:15:34,162 --> 00:15:36,528
-[ PANTING, GASPS ]

319
00:15:36,528 --> 00:15:40,528
-[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

320
00:15:40,528 --> 00:15:43,028
-[ WHIMPERS LIGHTLY ]

321
00:15:43,028 --> 00:15:44,328
-MYTHO.

322
00:15:48,362 --> 00:15:51,362
[ WHIMPERS LIGHTLY ]

323
00:15:51,362 --> 00:15:54,362
-WON'T YOU DANCE WITH ME?

324
00:15:54,362 --> 00:15:57,862
WHY ARE YOU SO...
SO FRIGHTENED OF ME?!

325
00:15:57,862 --> 00:15:59,862
AAAAAH!
-[ GASPS ]

326
00:15:59,862 --> 00:16:01,695
HE'S RIGHT.

327
00:16:01,695 --> 00:16:05,362
JUST NOW,
I WAS...AFRAID OF MYTHO.

328
00:16:05,362 --> 00:16:06,695
-WHOA! SCARY!

329
00:16:06,695 --> 00:16:07,862
-OH!
-AAH!

330
00:16:07,862 --> 00:16:09,362
-[ PANTING ]

331
00:16:09,362 --> 00:16:11,395
[ CROWS CAWING ]

332
00:16:15,762 --> 00:16:19,195
-[ WHIMPERS ]

333
00:16:19,195 --> 00:16:20,662
[ GASPS ]

334
00:16:22,628 --> 00:16:23,895
THE PRINCE!

335
00:16:25,928 --> 00:16:27,395
[ WHOOSH ]

336
00:16:31,862 --> 00:16:34,028
-[ GRUNTS ]

337
00:16:34,028 --> 00:16:35,928
KRAEHE, DANCE WITH ME.

338
00:16:35,928 --> 00:16:37,928
-[ WHIMPERS LIGHTLY ]

339
00:16:37,928 --> 00:16:39,595
-[ GROANS ]

340
00:16:39,595 --> 00:16:42,562
WHEN I'M NOT DANCING
WITH SOMEONE,

341
00:16:42,562 --> 00:16:44,428
I'M UNEASY AND LONELY.

342
00:16:44,428 --> 00:16:48,262
AND IT HURTS SO MUCH,
I CAN'T STAND IT.

343
00:16:48,262 --> 00:16:50,428
-MY PRINCE.

344
00:16:50,428 --> 00:16:53,428
I'M SORRY, MY PRINCE.

345
00:16:53,428 --> 00:16:57,262
YOU'RE SUFFERING
BECAUSE OF THE RAVEN'S BLOOD.

346
00:16:57,262 --> 00:16:59,605
THE HEARTS OF THESE BIRDS
HURT PEOPLE.

347
00:17:03,724 --> 00:17:05,158
-OH.

348
00:17:05,158 --> 00:17:07,991
-EVEN THE PEOPLE YOU LOVE.

349
00:17:07,991 --> 00:17:14,491
THE MORE LOVE YOU HAVE FOR THEM,
THE MORE PAIN YOU CAUSE THEM.

350
00:17:14,491 --> 00:17:17,558
WITH MY OWN HANDS,
I'VE THROWN INTO CHAOS

351
00:17:17,558 --> 00:17:20,591
THIS HEART OF YOURS
THAT LOVES EVERYONE.

352
00:17:20,591 --> 00:17:23,324
[ Voice breaking ] EVERY PART
OF THIS HAS BEEN MY FAULT,

353
00:17:23,324 --> 00:17:27,124
JUST BECAUSE I WANTED TO HAVE
YOUR LOVE ALL TO MYSELF.

354
00:17:27,124 --> 00:17:29,658
I'M SO SORRY.
-RUE.

355
00:17:29,658 --> 00:17:32,158
-[ GASPS ] TUTU.

356
00:17:32,158 --> 00:17:35,424
-THIS PENDANT THAT TRANSFORMS ME
INTO PRINCESS TUTU

357
00:17:35,424 --> 00:17:38,091
IS ALSO A SHARD
FROM THE PRINCE'S HEART,

358
00:17:38,091 --> 00:17:40,058
SO IT IS THE WILL
OF THE PRINCE HIMSELF

359
00:17:40,058 --> 00:17:42,124
TO HAVE ALL OF HIS HEART
RETURNED TO HIM.

360
00:17:44,158 --> 00:17:47,324
I'LL ACT ACCORDING
TO THE PRINCE'S WILL.

361
00:17:47,324 --> 00:17:51,258
LET'S BOTH BELIEVE
IN THE PRINCE.

362
00:17:51,258 --> 00:17:53,624
-ALL RIGHT, THEN.

363
00:18:00,091 --> 00:18:02,824
-[ Thinking ] SHARDS, ENTER ME.

364
00:18:02,824 --> 00:18:05,324
HERE I AM!

365
00:18:05,324 --> 00:18:07,291
[ HIGH-PITCHED WHIRRING ]

366
00:18:16,091 --> 00:18:17,324
[ DOORS CREAK ]

367
00:18:17,324 --> 00:18:19,824
[ DOORS CREAK ]

368
00:18:19,824 --> 00:18:23,291
[ WHIRRING RESUMES ]

369
00:18:23,291 --> 00:18:25,758
[ RUMBLING ]

370
00:18:31,791 --> 00:18:33,791
-LOOK AT WHAT YOU'VE BECOME.

371
00:18:33,791 --> 00:18:36,291
-SO, THIS IS THE PRINCE?
HOW LAMENTABLE.

372
00:18:36,291 --> 00:18:37,791
-WHAT?

373
00:18:37,791 --> 00:18:41,791
-DOESN'T IT SEEM
LIKE IT'S ALREADY TOO LATE?

374
00:18:41,791 --> 00:18:44,524
-WHAT CAN WE DO BUT RETURN
TO OUR ORIGINAL HEART?

375
00:18:44,524 --> 00:18:46,791
-LET'S PREPARE OURSELVES.

376
00:18:46,791 --> 00:18:49,791
THE RAVEN IS ABOUT TO REVIVE.
LET US NOT WAVER.

377
00:18:49,791 --> 00:18:51,791
[ TWINKLING ]

378
00:18:51,791 --> 00:18:53,458
-[ GASPS ]

379
00:18:53,458 --> 00:18:56,024
-PRINCESS TUTU, THANK YOU.

380
00:18:56,024 --> 00:19:00,024
HOWEVER, IF EVEN AFTER
I GO BACK INSIDE MY HEART

381
00:19:00,024 --> 00:19:02,791
AND THE RAVEN'S CURSE
HAS NOT BEEN LIFTED...

382
00:19:02,791 --> 00:19:04,258
-WHAT?

383
00:19:04,258 --> 00:19:07,358
-...I ASK YOU, YOU PLEASE NOT
RETURN THE FINAL HEART SHARD.

384
00:19:07,358 --> 00:19:08,791
-BUT I...

385
00:19:08,791 --> 00:19:13,791
-IF THAT HAPPENS, PLEASE FIND
A WAY TO LIFT THE CURSE QUICKLY.

386
00:19:13,791 --> 00:19:15,291
-BUT THAT'S --

387
00:19:15,291 --> 00:19:17,958
-WE DON'T HAVE
A MOMENT TO SPARE NOW.

388
00:19:17,958 --> 00:19:19,958
[ TWINKLE ]
-[ GASPS ]

389
00:19:19,958 --> 00:19:22,958
IF THAT IS WHAT
THE PRINCE WILLS.

390
00:19:22,958 --> 00:19:24,791
[ GRUNTS LIGHTLY ]

391
00:19:24,791 --> 00:19:27,458
[ TWINKLING ]

392
00:19:27,458 --> 00:19:29,458
-[ GASPS ]

393
00:19:29,458 --> 00:19:30,791
[ GROANING ]

394
00:19:30,791 --> 00:19:32,791
-MY PRINCE!
-[ GASPS ]

395
00:19:32,791 --> 00:19:35,624
[ RUMBLING, THUNDER BOOMING ]

396
00:19:35,624 --> 00:19:39,524
-[ GROANING ]

397
00:19:39,524 --> 00:19:42,524
-[ GASPS ]

398
00:19:42,524 --> 00:19:47,524
-PRINCE...WE FINALLY MEET AGAIN.

399
00:19:47,524 --> 00:19:49,524
-SO THIS IS THE RAVEN.

400
00:19:49,524 --> 00:19:53,524
-NOW, KRAEHE,
BRING THE PRINCE HERE.

401
00:19:53,524 --> 00:19:54,858
-[ WHIMPERS LIGHTLY ]

402
00:19:54,858 --> 00:19:56,024
NO!

403
00:19:56,024 --> 00:19:58,024
-WHAT?

404
00:19:58,024 --> 00:20:00,958
THEN YOU DON'T MIND
LOSING MY LOVE?

405
00:20:00,958 --> 00:20:04,524
-MY FATHER IS NO RAVEN!
AND AS FOR YOU, YOU'RE A LIAR!

406
00:20:04,524 --> 00:20:06,524
-HMM. [ CHUCKLES ]

407
00:20:06,524 --> 00:20:08,191
YOU FOUND OUT.

408
00:20:08,191 --> 00:20:10,324
I RAISED YOU
DRINKING MY NOBLE BLOOD

409
00:20:10,324 --> 00:20:11,824
EVER SINCE YOU WERE A BABY.

410
00:20:11,824 --> 00:20:15,224
BUT IN THE END, YOU'RE NOTHING
MORE THAN A FOOLISH HUMAN GIRL.

411
00:20:15,224 --> 00:20:18,058
IT'S BAD ENOUGH YOU COULDN'T
TURN THE PRINCE'S AFFECTIONS

412
00:20:18,058 --> 00:20:20,024
TOWARDS YOU
LIKE YOUR BLOOD DEMANDED,

413
00:20:20,024 --> 00:20:21,891
BUT TO THINK
YOU SUCCUMBED TO LOVE.

414
00:20:21,891 --> 00:20:24,058
-I HAVE
NO NEED OF RAVEN'S BLOOD!

415
00:20:24,058 --> 00:20:27,258
WHEN I WAS RUE, I WAS RUE.

416
00:20:27,258 --> 00:20:29,158
THAT WAS WHEN I WAS HAPPIEST.

417
00:20:29,158 --> 00:20:31,158
-OH, RUE.

418
00:20:31,158 --> 00:20:33,824
-WHAT A WASTE OF MY TIME.

419
00:20:33,824 --> 00:20:37,491
NOW, PRINCE,
COME TO ME ON YOUR OWN POWER.

420
00:20:37,491 --> 00:20:40,324
GIVE ME YOUR HEART.

421
00:20:40,324 --> 00:20:41,658
-YOU MUSTN'T'!

422
00:20:41,658 --> 00:20:43,191
-[ CAWING ]

423
00:20:43,191 --> 00:20:45,691
-[ GASPS ] YOU MUSTN'T GO!

424
00:20:45,691 --> 00:20:47,224
-[ GASPS ]

425
00:20:47,224 --> 00:20:49,058
-NO! PLEASE DON'T GO!

426
00:20:49,058 --> 00:20:52,558
-[ CAWING ]
-DON'T GO!

427
00:20:52,558 --> 00:20:54,558
PRINCE!

428
00:20:54,558 --> 00:20:56,558
-PRINCE, PLEASE WAIT.

429
00:20:56,558 --> 00:20:58,558
-[ CAWS ] CAW!

430
00:20:58,558 --> 00:21:00,558
-AAAH! AAH!

431
00:21:00,558 --> 00:21:01,991
-[ LAUGHING EVILLY ]

432
00:21:01,991 --> 00:21:03,991
-NO! LET THE PRINCE GO!

433
00:21:03,991 --> 00:21:06,391
DON'T EAT THE PRINCE'S HEART!

434
00:21:06,391 --> 00:21:10,391
[ WHIMPERS ] LET HIM GO
AND EAT MY HEART INSTEAD!

435
00:21:10,391 --> 00:21:13,558
PLEASE! I LOVE YOU! MY PRINCE!

436
00:21:13,558 --> 00:21:16,558
I HAVE EVER SINCE I WAS LITTLE!

437
00:21:16,558 --> 00:21:18,391
I'VE ALWAYS LOVED YOU!

438
00:21:18,391 --> 00:21:20,924
[ WARBLING ]

439
00:21:27,891 --> 00:21:29,891
-[ GASPS ]
-[ GASPS ]

440
00:21:29,891 --> 00:21:33,391
-WHAT IS THIS FEELING I HAVE?

441
00:21:33,391 --> 00:21:35,424
-YOU DARE INTERFERE?

442
00:21:35,424 --> 00:21:37,991
-[ GRUNTS ]

443
00:21:37,991 --> 00:21:40,258
-THIS FRAIL, EARNEST LOVE.

444
00:21:40,258 --> 00:21:42,024
I MUST...

445
00:21:42,024 --> 00:21:44,358
-[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
-...I MUST PROTECT THIS LOVE.

446
00:21:47,624 --> 00:21:49,124
TUTU.

447
00:21:49,124 --> 00:21:52,124
TUTU, WERE YOU THE ONE
WHO HELPED ME?

448
00:21:52,124 --> 00:21:54,124
-MNH-MNH. [ GASPS ]

449
00:21:54,124 --> 00:21:55,391
-[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

450
00:21:55,391 --> 00:21:59,058
FOR YOU TO LOVE HIM SO MUCH,
YOU'D GIVE UP YOUR LIFE.

451
00:21:59,058 --> 00:22:03,058
YOU'RE A FOOLISH GIRL
TO THE END.

452
00:22:03,058 --> 00:22:05,058
[ CROWS CAWING ]

453
00:22:05,058 --> 00:22:08,091
[ RITSUKO OKAZAKI'S "ALTHOUGH
MY LOVE IS SMALL" PLAYS ]

454
00:22:18,158 --> 00:22:20,191
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

455
00:23:35,924 --> 00:23:39,558
-WHEN THAT HAPPENS, I'LL GO BACK
TO BEING JUST A BIRD,

456
00:23:39,558 --> 00:23:42,724
AND I WON'T EVER STUDY BALLET
WITH EVERYBODY AGAIN.

457
00:23:42,724 --> 00:23:44,324
-THAT'S FINE, ISN'T IT?

458
00:23:44,324 --> 00:23:45,991
AFTER ALL,
THAT'S WHO YOU REALLY ARE.

459
00:23:45,991 --> 00:23:48,758
-I WOULD LIKE FOR YOU
TO RETURN MY FINAL HEART SHARD.

460
00:23:48,758 --> 00:23:50,958
-SAY, UH,
I HAVE ANOTHER QUESTION.

461
00:23:50,958 --> 00:23:53,391
DO YOU THINK HE'LL LOVE ME?

462
00:23:53,391 --> 00:23:55,824
-LET'S GO BACK
TO BEING OUR TRUE SELVES NOW.

463
00:23:55,824 --> 00:23:57,991
-GOODBYE, NOW, MYTHO.

464
00:23:57,991 --> 00:23:59,158
GOODBYE.

465
00:23:59,158 --> 00:24:01,991
-ALL YOU CHILDREN
WHO LOVE STORIES,

466
00:24:01,991 --> 00:24:03,591
COME GATHER 'ROUND.

467
00:24:03,591 --> 00:24:04,924
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

